- **Re-anchoring** iteratively refines context representations during inference/training based on evolving relation predictions.
- **Transfer learning** provides task-aware initialization using knowledge from related tasks, with selective adaptation to current context.
- **Interactive attention** enables bidirectional, iterative alignment between text arguments, creating feedback loops that improve relational reasoning.

The synergy among these components aims to strengthen contextual grounding and relational inference, particularly under stress conditions like domain shifts or low-resource settings. Evaluation will include standard benchmarks (e.g., PDTB) and robustness tests. Initial experiments are suggested to begin with modular ablation studies before advancing to end-to-end training.
